            "questionText": "A climatologist is analyzing satellite data and determines that Earth's albedo has decreased from 0.3 to 0.28 over the past 50 years. Given that the solar constant $!$S$!$ is approximately 1400 $!$W/m^2$!$, calculate the percentage change in Earth's average intensity $!$I_{av}$!$ of absorbed solar radiation due to this change in albedo. Assume that the solar constant remains the same.",
